Heavy equipment manufacturer Caterpillar and Barloworld Equipment will open a joint parts center in Kaalfontein, Midrand, later this year. &ldquo;This facility interconnects with Barloworld Equipment&rsquo;s Vision 2020, which includes our goal of becoming the world&rsquo;s leading Caterpillar dealer,&rdquo; Barloworld Equipment Southern Africa CEO Emmy Leeka said. He noted that the new facility is a consolidation of two parts distribution centres and will enable the company to work more efficiently, while increasing the capability to provide parts availability to customers throughout Africa.